<https://typeclasses.com/ghc/type-operators>

```main.hs:40:7: error:
    Illegal symbol '.' in type
    Perhaps you intended to use RankNTypes or a similar language
    extension to enable explicit-forall syntax: forall <tvs>. <type>
   |
40 | type (.) = Compose
   |       ^```
<@U01A4JVLVNV> `assocAlterF` の型教えてもらっていいですか？

GHC 8.10.1のGHCiでできました。以下を貼り付けてね！
```:set -XTypeOperators

import Data.Functor.Compose

type (.) = Compose
:k (.)

:set -XDerivingVia
:{
newtype ReaderIO env a = ReaderIO (env -> IO a)
    deriving (Functor, Applicative) via ((->) env . IO)
:}
act = (ReaderIO putStrLn *> ReaderIO putStrLn)
ReaderIO act' = act
act' "hello"```
<https://github.com/ghc-proposals/ghc-proposals/blob/master/proposals/0143-remove-star-kind.rst>

Data.Map.Strict.alterFのエイリアスにしているのでalterFと同じで::(Functor f, <https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/Data-Ord.html#t:Ord|Ord> k) => (<https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/GHC-Maybe.html#t:Maybe|Maybe> a -> f (<https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/GHC-Maybe.html#t:Maybe|Maybe> a)) -> k -> <https://hackage.haskell.org/package/containers-0.6.3.1/docs/Data-Map-Strict.html#t:Map|Map> k a -> f (<https://hackage.haskell.org/package/containers-0.6.3.1/docs/Data-Map-Strict.html#t:Map|Map> k a)です

<https://downloads.haskell.org/ghc/8.8.1-alpha1/docs/html/users_guide/8.8.1-notes.html#language>
> `(!)` and `(.)` are now valid type operators:
